summary:
The Security Council,

Recalling resolutions 827 (1993) and 955 (1994) establishing the International Tribunal for the former Yugoslavia (ICTY) and the International Criminal Tribunal for Rwanda (ICTR), 

Recalling resolutions 1503 (2003) and 1534 (2004) on the Tribunals' completion strategy, 

Acknowledging the Tribunals' contribution to international criminal justice and accountability, 

Recalling the need to combat impunity for serious international crimes and bring all indicted persons to justice, 

Establishes the International Residual Mechanism for Criminal Tribunals (the Mechanism) with two branches, to commence on 1 July 2012 (ICTR) and 1 July 2013 (ICTY); 

 Adopts the Statute of the Mechanism in Annex 1; 

Decides on transitional arrangements in Annex 2; 

Requests the ICTY and ICTR to complete their remaining work by 31 December 2014 and ensure a smooth transition to the Mechanism; 

Decides that the Mechanism will continue the jurisdiction, rights, and obligations of the ICTY and ICTR; 

Requests the Secretary-General to submit draft Rules of Procedure and Evidence for the Mechanism; 

Decides on the Rules of Procedure and Evidence; 

Decides on the seats of the Mechanism's branches; 

Recalls States' obligation to cooperate with the Tribunals and the Mechanism; 

Decides that all States shall cooperate fully with the Mechanism.
The Security Council,

10. Urges all States, especially those where fugitives are suspected to be, to intensify cooperation with and render assistance to the Tribunals and the Mechanism to achieve the arrest and surrender of remaining fugitives;

11. Urges the Tribunals and the Mechanism to refer cases not involving senior leaders to national jurisdictions;

12. Calls upon all States to cooperate to receive referred cases;

13. Requests the Secretary-General to implement this resolution and make arrangements for the Mechanism's effective functioning from the first commencement date, and to initiate procedures for selecting judges by 30 June 2011;

14. Requests the Secretary-General to prepare an information security and access regime for the archives;

15. Requests the Tribunals and the Mechanism to cooperate with countries and entities to facilitate information and documentation centres;

16. Requests the President of the Mechanism to submit annual and six-monthly reports;

17. Decides the Mechanism shall operate for an initial four-year period, reviewed every two years;
